{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17586088","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17586088"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:25:52+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:25:52+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15059"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15059","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15059"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7747"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67752"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7747","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7747"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15059"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53217"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8115"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18914"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18919"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67752","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67752"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDiabetic nephropathy involves several metabolic pathways that lead to characteristic glomerular basement membrane thickening.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes an indirect mechanism causing glomerular basement membrane thickening in diabetic nephropathy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Protein kinase C activation leading to TGF-beta production","Non-enzymatic glycation of basement membrane proteins","Increased sorbitol accumulation","Direct matrix protein synthesis","Oxidative stress from free radical formation"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is \u003Cstrong\u003Eprotein kinase C activation leading to TGF-beta production\u003C/strong\u003E. This represents an indirect pathway where hyperglycemia activates protein kinase C, which then increases TGF-beta expression. TGF-beta subsequently stimulates matrix protein production, leading to basement membrane thickening.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other mechanisms are direct pathways:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENon-enzymatic glycation of basement membrane proteins\u003C/strong\u003E directly modifies and cross-links proteins in the basement membrane\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased sorbitol accumulation\u003C/strong\u003E through the polyol pathway directly causes osmotic stress and cellular damage\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirect matrix protein synthesis\u003C/strong\u003E immediately contributes to basement membrane thickening without intermediate steps\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOxidative stress from free radical formation\u003C/strong\u003E directly damages cellular components\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding these pathways is crucial as they represent potential therapeutic targets in diabetic nephropathy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Protein kinase C activation by hyperglycemia leads to increased TGF-beta expression, which indirectly causes glomerular basement membrane thickening","Multiple pathways contribute to diabetic nephropathy including direct protein glycation, polyol pathway activation, and oxidative stress","Glomerular basement membrane thickening is a hallmark pathological feature of diabetic nephropathy"],"references":["Pourghasem M, Shafi H, Babazadeh Z. Histological changes of kidney in diabetic nephropathy. Caspian J Intern Med. 2015 Summer;6(3):120-7. PMID: 26644877; PMCID: PMC4650785.","Ayodele OE, Alebiosu CO. Burden of chronic kidney disease: an international perspective. Adv Chronic Kidney Dis. 2010 May;17(3):215-24. doi: 10.1053/j.ackd.2010.02.001. PMID: 20439090.","Jennette, J. C., \u0026 D\u0027Agati, V. D. (2023). Heptinstall\u0027s Pathology of the Kidney. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Koeppen, B. M., \u0026 Stanton, B. A. (2018). Renal Physiology E-Book: Renal Physiology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53217"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15059"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53217","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53217"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-06T22:14:19+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-06T22:15:36+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7747"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67752"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null